<h2><strong>PACER&rsquo;s Simon Technology Center to host Family  Fun Day on Sept. 23</strong></h2>
<p>Minneapolis: On  Saturday, Sept. 23, PACER&rsquo;s Simon Technology Center will provide an exciting  opportunity to try out the latest in assistive technology, including adapted  toys, 3D printers, robots, and more, and see firsthand how life-changing these  devices can be! </p>
<p>The Simon Technology Center&rsquo;s annual Family Fun Day  and Tech Expo is a free community event that will feature fun activities for  all ages and abilities. Participants can interact with a variety of devices for  children, teens, and adults. </p>
<p>PACER staff and volunteers will provide hands-on  activities as well as opportunities to learn about a wide range of assistive  technology that can help individuals from birth to adulthood gain independence.  There will be mini sessions to see iPad app demonstrations, accessible art and  do-it-yourself technology, information about PACER&rsquo;s resources, and light  refreshments.</p>
<p>Children and youth with disabilities, their  families, and professionals are encouraged to attend.</p>
<p>&ldquo;Our Family Fun Day is a  great time to see what we have to offer,&rdquo; said Bridget Gilormini, director of  PACER&rsquo;s Simon Technology Center. &ldquo;Visitors can meet our staff and see the many  ways we help children and families be successful at home, at school, and in the  community with assistive technology.&rdquo;</p>
<blockquote>
<p>WHAT: PACER&rsquo;s  Simon Technology Center Family Fun Day and Tech Exp0</p>
<p>WHEN: Saturday,  Sept. 23, from 10 a.m. to 2 p.m.</p>
<p>WHERE: PACER Center, 8161 Normandale  Blvd., Bloomington </p>
</blockquote>
<p>This event is free and advance registration is  required; go to <a href="http://www.pacer.org/workshops">PACER.org/workshops</a> or call PACER at (952) 838-9000. In greater Minnesota, call (800) 537-2237. </p>
